programme.title: How Do They Do It?

programme.title: How Do They Do It? Met Teun en Joep

programme.title: NASA's Unexplained Files
programme.desc: Een foto van Apollo 17 lijkt een Amerikaanse militaire buitenpost op de maan te laten zien. Een onderzoek naar het leven in de oceanen van de manen van Jupiter. Ten slotte laat de documentaire zien aan welk gevaar Neil Armstrong werd blootgesteld.

programme.title: NASA's Unexplained Files
programme.desc: Als een Chinese maanrover afbreekt, wijst een NASA-wetenschapper op mysterieus materiaal dat de Apollo-missies, tientallen jaren eerder, leek te saboteren. Ruimtevaartuig Rosetta ontdekt een planeet die lijkt te zingen.

programme.title: NASA's Unexplained Files
programme.desc: Uit recent ontdekte documenten blijkt dat NASA een reserveplan had voor als de eerste maanlanding zou mislukken en de Cassini-missie van NASA onthult een 300 jaar oud mysterie.

programme.title: Cooper's Treasure
programme.desc: Darrell gaat op zoek naar een wrak van Gordo's lijst. Hij leidt zijn team naar ondiepe wateren waar eeuwenlang schepen ten prooi zijn gevallen aan de wind en de golven.

programme.title: Cooper's Treasure
programme.desc: Na bij de kust bewijs te hebben gevonden van een 18e-eeuwse reddingsboot, ontdekt Darrells team van welk wrak de boot kwam. Maar dan wordt de expeditie door een tragedie getroffen.

programme.title: How Do They Do It?

programme.title: How Do They Do It?

programme.title: How Do They Do It?

programme.title: NASA's Unexplained Files

programme.title: Graveyard Carz

With time flying and stress mounting the team works long hours and weekends trying to finish this iconic build. With SEMA only days away, the A100 finally gets its iconic 426 HEMI engine, well, if they can make it fit!

programme.title: Graveyard Carz
programme.sub-title: Night of the Little Dead Wagon

With the A100 finished the team heads out to SEMA in order to roll the Little Dead Wagon over the red carpet for Mopar and Mark once again receives a very kind gift from our friends.

programme.title: Graveyard Carz

The collection was put together by their unnamed father. Seller agrees to have Dale broker rare Excelsior for high-end client. Dale has the buyer, but will he outbid his own client for the exclusive find?

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Matt is out for revenge. Last year Dale beat him badly at the Annual Vintage bike race in Barber, Alabama. But this year there is a whole new tale to tell. With just days until the race - Dale is secretly struggling to get the bike he beat Matt with last year up and working. Matt struggles just to locate a 100-year old bike. Matt's prayers are answered thanks to an old Catholic Priest he located who has possession of a bike. The priest might let Matt have the bike to race - but there are conditions. The toughest one: Don't tell Dale you have it. Can Matt afford to buy the bike and get it running in time for the race without Dale seeing it? Will Dale even get his broken bike started? And if they ever get to race, will Matt exact his revenge?

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Built in the mid-60s by eccentric engineer Wild Bill Gelbke, the Road Dog was, and still is, the largest motorcycle ever built. It utilized aircraft tubing, Corvette disc brakes, and a Chevy truck differential to keep it stable. The one-off creation disappeared when Gelbke did in 1978. Outflanked once when the bike was spotted and sold to a private collector in 1995, Dale has vowed to locate the machine and make Wheels Through Time its final resting place.

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Big Time Motorcycle Auction

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: The RM Auction Company has worked with Dale before as a buyer, seller, historian, and caretaker at the prestigious Lee Hartung auction. But this event is no last minute rush to define one mans treasures. This is a well calculated, time consuming, multi-media, and multi motorcycle and prized art deal.

programme.title: What's In the Barn?
programme.desc: Home Depot Senior Vice President, Gordon Erickson, is a huge fan of Wheels Through Time. He is also a huge supporter of the Wounded Warrior program.
